# Nerd Font icon map -- shared source of truth for both rofi
# (nerdfont-launcher.py) and Awesome (theme/icons.lua).
#
# Format: key|glyph[|class_override]
#   key            lowercase text matched as a substring against the app's
#                  rofi .desktop Name AND the window's WM_CLASS (both sides
#                  normalized: lowercased, spaces/hyphens/dots stripped).
#   glyph          paste the Nerd Font glyph here. Leave empty for now.
#   class_override only needed when the running window's WM_CLASS shares no
#                  substring with `key` (e.g. Blueman-manager vs "Bluetooth
#                  Manager"). Optional, third column.
#
# Matching tries the LONGEST key first, so specific entries (e.g.
# "datagrip") always win over generic ones (e.g. "toolbox") -- you don't
# need to worry about line order when adding new apps.
#
# KNOWN LIMITATIONS:
# - All LibreOffice modules (Writer/Calc/Draw/Impress/Math/Base) share the
#   same WM_CLASS "soffice". Awesome's tasklist can only show ONE icon for
#   any LibreOffice window regardless of module; rofi shows them correctly.
# - ranger and htop run with Terminal=true: in Awesome their WM_CLASS is
#   whatever terminal launched them (Alacritty), not their own.

